Air France Hedges 53% of 2011 Fuel Needs at $111 Brent Crude

-- B y   R a c h e l   G r a h a m
-- 
2011-05-19T13:47:59Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-19/air-france-hedges-53-of-2011-fuel-needs-at-111-brent-crude-1-.html
Air France-KLM (AF)  Group, Europeâ€™s
biggest airline, said it hedged 53 percent of its fuel needs for
this year and 49 percent for this quarter.  The carrier is hedged for this year at an average price of
$111 a barrel using Brent crude, according to a presentation
posted on its  website . The Paris-based airline is covered at
$117 a barrel for this quarter, the data showed.  Hedging allows airlines to agree on prices for expected
fuel needs, helping to guard against cost fluctuations. Brent
traded at about $112 a barrel today on the ICE Futures exchange
in  London .  Air France is 55 percent hedged at $112 a barrel from July
to September and 58 percent at $111 for the following three
months, the presentation showed. Jet fuel in northwest  Europe 
averaged $1,000 a metric ton this year, according to data
compiled by Bloomberg.  To contact the reporter on this story:
